♪You said you would be with me♪

13
00:01:32,260 --> 00:01:35,180
=Six Sisters=

14
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 31=

15
00:02:13,940 --> 00:02:17,060
Grandma, why do you want
to come here today?

16
00:02:19,660 --> 00:02:23,740
Along the river lies our hometown.

17
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:35,860
- Nice cake.
- This is Great-grandma.

18
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:36,810
The birthday lady.

19
00:03:36,820 --> 00:03:38,140
She's the queen of our family.

20
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:40,500
Don't be ridiculous.

21
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,340
You're so good at making stuff up.

22
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,060
Why don't you be a writer?

23
00:03:47,380 --> 00:03:49,460
If you can't say anything nice, shut up.

24
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:52,060
Great-grandma is
the head of this family.

25
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:53,220
She's our backbone.

26
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:55,820
She's our central pillar.

27
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:56,940
This is my grandma,

28
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:58,060
the mother of six girls.

29
00:03:58,540 --> 00:04:00,300
Yes. I have six daughters.

30
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,900
That's all I've done.

31
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:04,060
This is my eldest aunt.

32
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:06,340
She's hardworking.
Everybody listens to her.

33
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:07,660
Nobody listens to me now.

34
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:09,500
This is her husband, a retired cadre.

35
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:14,620
This is my cousin and his wife.

36
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,220
A perfect couple Tianjia'an.

37
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:17,500
Oh, come on.

38
00:04:20,020 --> 00:04:20,940
This is my second aunt,

39
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,340
the prettiest lady.

40
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:23,940
Uncle Fan isn't here, huh?

41
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:25,660
No. He's on duty today.

42
00:04:26,860 --> 00:04:27,740
This is my mother.

43
00:04:27,860 --> 00:04:28,700
She's very artistic.

44
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:29,740
I got my artistic genes

45
00:04:29,740 --> 00:04:31,660
totally from her.

46
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:33,860
If you inherited even one-third,

47
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,300
you would be an artist.

48
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:36,940
This is my father,

49
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:37,980
born in the Year of the Tiger.

50
00:04:38,060 --> 00:04:39,340
He used to be powerful and rich.

51
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:40,540
But now, he has a hard time.

52
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:43,460
Now, you can use idioms.

53
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:45,940
This is my fourth aunt.

54
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:48,660
She's a talented leader
who has dozens of subordinates.

55
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:49,700
She makes the most money.

56
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:52,700
Not really. I get paid monthly.

57
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,450
That's good enough.

58
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:56,700
It's so hard to do business now.

59
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:59,020
This is my sixth aunt,

60
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:00,820
a modern lady.

61
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:02,340
This is her husband

62
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:04,140
who loves tea eggs.

63
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:05,540
Oh, no.

64
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:06,460
I'm labeled.

65
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:07,420
"Love tea eggs."

66
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:10,340
This is my second cousin.

67
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:12,020
And the other two cousins

68
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:13,900
both study better than I do.

69
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:15,420
Aren't you ashamed?

70
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,500
What's your name?

71
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:21,700
Go there.

72
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,540
Hello.

73
00:05:24,060 --> 00:05:24,900
Ok.

74
00:05:25,770 --> 00:05:27,460
Grandma, it's Xiaoling.

75
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,060
Oh, she's on the phone?

76
00:05:30,460 --> 00:05:31,340
Xiaoling.

77
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:32,940
Aunt Xiaoling?

78
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:36,100
Yes. How's everything there?

79
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:37,020
Xiaoling?

80
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,260
All right.

81
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:41,060
Talk to your mother.

82
00:05:42,540 --> 00:05:43,380
Hello.

83
00:05:44,460 --> 00:05:45,500
Ok. Ok.

84
00:05:45,860 --> 00:05:47,620
We're celebrating
your grandma's birthday.

85
00:05:48,020 --> 00:05:49,220
Alright. Got it.

86
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:50,580
- Wait.
- Say something.

87
00:05:50,940 --> 00:05:52,180
Yangyang, don't run away.

88
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:53,260
I won't.

89
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,140
Mom.

90
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:58,100
Yes.

91
00:05:59,620 --> 00:06:00,460
Everybody is here.

92
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:04,300
Everything's fine. Don't worry.

93
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,540
She hung up?

94
00:06:07,980 --> 00:06:08,820
Fine.

95
00:06:10,050 --> 00:06:10,890
Jiayi.

96
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:11,900
Come and have the cake.

97
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:12,980
- Hurry.
- Here.

98
00:06:13,180 --> 00:06:14,460
I'll light the candle.

99
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:21,090
Come on.

100
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:22,660
Grandma, make a wish.

101
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:26,500
I don't need to make a wish at this age.

102
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,460
- You do.
- Say something nice.

103
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:30,620
In this case,

104
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:33,860
I hope our family will prosper

105
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:35,540
and you guys will be united.

106
00:06:35,940 --> 00:06:36,780
Jiali.

107
00:06:36,780 --> 00:06:40,340
You and your sisters must
take care of your mom when she's old.

108
00:06:40,460 --> 00:06:42,940
Don't worry. Dad told us
what to do before he died.

109
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:44,300
Jianguo takes care of this family.

110
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:45,580
Jianguo.

111
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:48,340
I'll be relieved, then.

112
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,660
Blow out the candle.

113
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:52,980
Let's sing the birthday song.

114
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:56,540
♪Happy birthday to you♪

115
00:06:56,780 --> 00:07:00,180
♪Happy birthday to you♪

116
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:03,900
♪Happy birthday to you♪

117
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:07,860
♪Happy birthday to you♪

118
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:11,580
Try again.

119
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:16,460
Blow higher.

120
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:22,340
Naughty boy.

121
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:23,860
The noodles are ready.

122
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:26,740
Come on.

123
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:27,740
Be careful, Mom.

124
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:29,660
Come here.

125
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:35,220
Ms. Liu's son Zhang Qiulin

126
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:37,780
went back to Hefei and got remarried.

127
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,660
Jiali, I'll say it one last time.

128
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,260
My divorce with Fang Tao

129
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:46,700
has nothing to do with Qiulin.

130
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:50,940
People

131
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:53,820
should keep a low profile.

132
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:56,620
Too much arrogance may make you fall.

133
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:02,700
It's ok.

134
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:03,820
Pieces for peace.

135
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:04,660
Come on. Step aside.

136
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:06,300
All right, Jiayi.

137
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,500
You go east and I go west.

138
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,540
See you, then.

139
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:09,580
I'll go west, too.

140
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:10,620
Let me go with you.

141
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,140
Why?

142
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,740
I'll go see your mother-in-law.

143
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,930
Why?

144
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:18,690
I quarreled with someone in the market.

145
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:21,100
Your mother-in-law stood up for me.

146
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,500
I'm quite grateful.

147
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:24,500
Oh, come on.

148
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:26,540
What kind of tank do you like,

149
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:27,380
Xinxin?

150
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:29,580
- Mom.
- This one...

151
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:30,420
Hi, ma'am.

152
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,820
Oh, Jiayi. What are you doing here?

153
00:08:34,860 --> 00:08:36,220
I'm here to see you.

154
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:37,940
Last time in the market,

155
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:39,220
glad you helped me.

156
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:41,700
Or I would have fought with that guy.

157
00:08:41,820 --> 00:08:43,100
Relatives like us should

158
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,020
help each other. Don't say that.

159
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:45,980
Take your seat.

160
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:48,900
Who is this kid?

161
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,660
Mom's grandson.

162
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:52,740
- Right.
- Oh, I see.

163
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:54,140
He has a perfect nose

164
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:55,300
and big eyes.

165
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,700
Such a pretty boy.

166
00:08:58,660 --> 00:09:00,620
Come on. Have some fruit.

167
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:02,220
You needn't have come

168
00:09:02,220 --> 00:09:03,500
with the fruit.

169
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:05,140
It's my pleasure.

170
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:06,620
- Here, ma'am.
- Ok. Thanks.

171
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,100
- And you?
- I want an orange, Jiayi.

172
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:08,940
- Orange, huh?
- Mm.

173
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:11,820
You have some, too.

174
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:12,940
Alright. I will.

175
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,420
I'll have a banana, then.

176
00:09:16,540 --> 00:09:17,900
He's a good boy.

177
00:09:18,420 --> 00:09:19,500
But he can't live here.

178
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,980
Ma'am, no offense.

179
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:26,140
All kinds of people live

180
00:09:26,140 --> 00:09:27,900
near the train station.

181
00:09:28,420 --> 00:09:29,700
If a kid grows up here,

182
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,020
his life will be ruined.

183
00:09:33,060 --> 00:09:35,620
Where else can we live, then?

184
00:09:36,060 --> 00:09:38,860
Besides, this is our ancestral estate.

185
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:40,420
Our next-door neighbors

186
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:42,260
have been informed by superiors.

187
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:43,820
They'll move away

188
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:45,420
and return their rooms to us.

189
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:47,540
That's really wonderful, huh?

190
00:09:47,540 --> 00:09:49,140
This is my house, after all.

191
00:09:50,180 --> 00:09:52,260
Then, you can sell this house.

192
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:55,060
Isn't it great to live in a flat?

193
00:09:57,220 --> 00:09:59,940
The flats in the community

194
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,220
are really good.

195
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:03,620
But this house is old.

196
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:04,660
Who will buy it?

197
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:08,440
You know what?

198
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:12,150
My husband is Jiaxi's brother-in-law.

199
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:15,860
How shall I put it?

200
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:20,580
He has a lot of brothers

201
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:21,560
who can't afford to live.

202
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:23,060
So, I'm thinking

203
00:10:23,340 --> 00:10:25,300
I can buy a house for them

204
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:26,860
to serve breakfast

205
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:28,060
or sell tea eggs.

206
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:29,460
They can make a living, anyway.

207
00:10:30,660 --> 00:10:32,220
I'm not like Jiaxi.

208
00:10:33,260 --> 00:10:35,180
She has a capable husband

209
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:37,860
and a helpful mother-in-law like you.

210
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:40,940
Our bathhouse has closed down.

211
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:43,650
We can only live on my layoff salary.

212
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,340
I even have to spare some money

213
00:10:46,460 --> 00:10:48,260
for my brothers-in-law and relatives.

214
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:50,180
Think about it, ma'am.

215
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:52,180
How am I supposed to live

216
00:10:52,180 --> 00:10:53,340
like that?

217
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:55,780
You really have a hard time.

218
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:58,100
How about you sell this house to me?

219
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:10,740
The point is I can't decide this.

220
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:13,140
Everybody knows that.

221
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:15,700
You're in charge of this family.

222
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:20,780
Well, the house price...

223
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:21,980
It's not a problem.

224
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:24,580
Quote us on the price.
Even if we have to sell everything

225
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:25,580
to collect the money,

226
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:28,260
we'll give you a good offer.

227
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:30,500
Fine.

228
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:32,380
I'll think about it.

229
00:11:36,540 --> 00:11:39,020
You're so good at doing trickery.

230
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:40,060
When you want her house,

231
00:11:40,060 --> 00:11:41,820
you should have at least told me.

232
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:43,760
I didn't mean to buy it.

233
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,100
We just brought that topic up.

234
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:47,660
That's a shabby house.

235
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:48,620
Will you really buy it?

236
00:11:49,260 --> 00:11:50,260
I have no choice.

237
00:11:50,620 --> 00:11:51,660
Ouyang has so many brothers

238
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:52,500
who have no food.

239
00:11:53,220 --> 00:11:54,660
As their sister-in-law,

240
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:56,220
I can't just watch them

241
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:57,260
starve to death.

242
00:11:57,820 --> 00:11:59,500
What if she asks for a lot of money?

243
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:01,820
She won't.

244
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:05,300
You and Hongyu will help.

245
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:07,340
She and I are relatives.

246
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:10,220
She wants to sell it
and I want to buy it.

247
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:11,620
The two of us

248
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:13,260
will both benefit.

249
00:12:13,980 --> 00:12:16,220
So, who'll benefit more?

250
00:12:16,660 --> 00:12:17,760
Don't be ridiculous.

251
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:34,260
- Honey, you're back.
- Honey.

252
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:38,280
I want to say something.

253
00:12:42,940 --> 00:12:43,780
What is it?

254
00:12:48,140 --> 00:12:49,420
Do you want to rise again?

255
00:12:50,620 --> 00:12:51,620
Isn't that obvious?

256
00:12:51,620 --> 00:12:54,580
Answer me. Yes or no.

257
00:12:54,820 --> 00:12:55,900
Yes, of course.

258
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:56,740
Good.

259
00:12:57,020 --> 00:13:00,940
We must take the plunge.

260
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:04,990
How?

261
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:11,020
Sell this house.

262
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:18,280
This house?

263
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:21,980
Yes. Our home. This house.

264
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:32,380
Here.

265
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:36,740
Congrats, Ms. Wang.

266
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,320
I should congratulate you, Ms. He.

267
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:40,980
Wish you a booming business

268
00:13:40,980 --> 00:13:41,860
and a big fortune.

269
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:43,880
You made a wise decision.

270
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,060
In a better place,

271
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,780
your grandson will make a difference.

272
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:48,740
What's the saying again?

273
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:51,220
In ancient times, a mother... What?

274
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:53,980
She relocated three times for her son.

275
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:55,580
Now, Ms. Wang

276
00:13:55,780 --> 00:13:57,980
has chosen a better place
for her descendants.

277
00:13:58,150 --> 00:13:59,860
Very wise, indeed.

278
00:14:00,140 --> 00:14:01,600
From your lips to God's ears.

279
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:08,820
(Property Sale and Purchase Contract)

280
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:11,350
Let's go, Jiayi.

281
00:14:12,270 --> 00:14:13,780
You're grinning from ear to ear.

282
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:16,740
Fine. We'll be neighbors.

283
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,490
Don't worry. You go through your door.

284
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,170
I've warned

285
